You're off the hook today,
but watch out.

00:13:37.233 --> 00:13:39.193
Lord Damian!

00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:46.200
[TWILIGHT]
How could this happen?!

00:13:46.242 --> 00:13:49.203
He totally rejected her apology?

00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:54.125
[TWILIGHT]
Plan B is DOA.

00:13:58.504 --> 00:14:00.465
Lord Damian, why are we running?

00:14:00.506 --> 00:14:02.925
Shut up!

00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:07.513
School's so scary.

00:14:07.555 --> 00:14:09.474
Help, Becky!

00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:11.351
Hello?!

00:14:11.392 --> 00:14:17.148
Whoever called me way out here
better start talking, okay?

00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:20.234
[TWILIGHT] The denominator
is three, so one third,

00:14:20.276 --> 00:14:23.029
and if you had three thirds,
it would be equal to one.

00:14:23.071 --> 00:14:23.821
Easy, huh?

00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:27.241
Uh, you know, maybe it's time
to take a little break?

00:14:27.283 --> 00:14:30.119
Not now. We have to get
through all of this today.

00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:31.037
[ANYA gasps]

00:14:31.079 --> 00:14:32.413
[TWILIGHT]
With their rocky start,

00:14:32.455 --> 00:14:34.207
plus that scene yesterday,

00:14:34.248 --> 00:14:36.417
I think we can forget about
the Friendship Scheme

00:14:36.459 --> 00:14:39.295
getting us in with the Desmonds.

00:14:39.337 --> 00:14:41.130
That ship has sailed.

00:14:41.172 --> 00:14:43.383
So the only solution at the
moment is to double down

00:14:43.424 --> 00:14:47.845
on the more orthodox method of
Plan A and earn those Stella.

00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:49.305
Finish this, Anya,

00:14:49.347 --> 00:14:52.642
or you can't watch your
spy cartoon tonight.

00:14:52.683 --> 00:14:54.685
Well? What's this answer?

00:14:54.727 --> 00:14:57.146
[ANYA] I'll just hafta
read Papa's mind for it.

00:14:57.188 --> 00:14:58.898
Come on. You use this
formula right here.

00:14:58.940 --> 00:14:59.982
[TWILIGHT]
There are a few other ways

00:15:00.024 --> 00:15:03.361
to get the eight Stella needed
to become an Imperial Scholar...

00:15:03.403 --> 00:15:05.863
To avoid getting Tonitrus
Bolts from bad grades

00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:07.240
and prevent expulsion,

00:15:07.281 --> 00:15:09.492
we're going to need to get
her academic skills up.

00:15:09.534 --> 00:15:10.868
I could enter the faculty room

00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:12.453
and alter her academic
documents,

00:15:12.495 --> 00:15:13.621
making her appear more--

00:15:13.663 --> 00:15:15.832
Oh, Anya, are you okay?

00:15:15.873 --> 00:15:18.126
[ANYA]
I'll read her mind instead.

00:15:18.167 --> 00:15:20.545
Mama, can you help me?

00:15:20.586 --> 00:15:23.339
Well, why don't we
look it over together?

00:15:23.381 --> 00:15:24.590
[YOR]
Let's see.

00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:27.802
The denominator is five,
so that's one split into five.

00:15:27.844 --> 00:15:28.511
Okay.

00:15:28.553 --> 00:15:32.306
For visualization, let's rip
all four limbs off of a torso.

00:15:32.348 --> 00:15:34.892
Hmm, but then the head's
getting in the way.

00:15:34.934 --> 00:15:38.062
Huh? Um, five. Five?

00:15:38.104 --> 00:15:40.648
Kinda weird how it
looks like an S.

00:15:44.694 --> 00:15:46.612
[YOR]
No! Anya, what's wrong?

00:15:46.654 --> 00:15:49.532
There a problem? Well?
Why can't you solve this?

00:15:49.574 --> 00:15:51.075
[TWILIGHT] I can't figure
out for the life of me

00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:52.660
what she's not getting.

00:15:52.702 --> 00:15:55.580
[ANYA]
I don't wanna study anymore!

00:15:55.621 --> 00:15:57.915
[TWILIGHT]
Hey! Wait a second!

00:15:57.957 --> 00:15:59.542
[YOR]
Um, Loid.

00:15:59.584 --> 00:16:01.627
I don't think it's a good
idea to be too forceful

00:16:01.669 --> 00:16:03.254
at times like this.

00:16:03.296 --> 00:16:07.049
Okay, but to be an Imperial
Scholar, she has to study.

00:16:07.091 --> 00:16:08.134
Yes, I know.

00:16:08.176 --> 00:16:11.596
Though is that actually
what Anya wants, or you?

00:16:13.264 --> 00:16:14.557
Well, uh...

00:16:14.599 --> 00:16:17.643
[TWILIGHT]
It's what the mission requires.

00:16:17.685 --> 00:16:20.897
Personally, I want Anya
to enjoy school

00:16:20.938 --> 00:16:22.899
and be excited to be there.

00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:24.192
Obviously, she'll have to study

00:16:24.233 --> 00:16:27.612
and keep her grades up
and all that, but...

00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:29.363
Of course, you're right.

00:16:29.405 --> 00:16:30.990
[TWILIGHT]
She's still so young.

00:16:31.032 --> 00:16:34.577
I'm sure getting good grades and
honors aren't her main concerns.

00:16:34.619 --> 00:16:36.245
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:16:36.287 --> 00:16:39.248
Not really my place to butt in
between you and your daughter.

00:16:39.290 --> 00:16:43.085
No, it's fine. I appreciate it.

00:16:43.127 --> 00:16:46.714
I do lose my cool a
little bit sometimes.

00:16:46.756 --> 00:16:49.675
[YOR] I'm sure other parents
go through the same thing.

00:16:49.717 --> 00:16:52.845
Let's try to relax.
I'll make some tea.

00:16:56.516 --> 00:17:00.228
[TWILIGHT]
Anya, we made you some cocoa.

00:17:02.355 --> 00:17:04.232
Seems she's holed up in there.

00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:07.401
Yeah, well, she's just
pouting a little.

00:17:13.783 --> 00:17:17.286
[ANYA] I promise,
I'll do my best at school!

00:17:20.540 --> 00:17:21.832
[YOR chuckles]

00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:24.377
She reminds me of my brother
when he was a kid.

00:17:24.418 --> 00:17:27.004
She'll come out before long.

00:17:27.046 --> 00:17:28.756
Oh, yeah, speaking of him,

00:17:28.798 --> 00:17:30.883
he works for Foreign
Affairs, right?

00:17:30.925 --> 00:17:32.843
Must've made good grades.

00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:35.638
So did you help him out
much with his homework?

00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.182
If you have any tips for me.

00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:39.183
Oh, no.

00:17:39.225 --> 00:17:41.686
And honestly, Yuri was always
a much better student

00:17:41.727 --> 00:17:43.312
than I ever was.

00:17:43.354 --> 00:17:45.856
Kind of embarrassing,
but he probably taught me

00:17:45.898 --> 00:17:47.233
more than I taught him.

00:17:47.275 --> 00:17:49.485
Whenever we would
study together...

00:17:49.527 --> 00:17:50.861
[YURI]
No, you might think so,

00:17:50.903 --> 00:17:54.073
but spiders actually aren't
insects, they're arachnids.

00:17:54.115 --> 00:17:56.659
They have eight legs,
and insects have six,

00:17:56.701 --> 00:17:57.868
and their bodies are split up

00:17:57.910 --> 00:18:00.580
between their head,
thorax, and abdomen.

00:18:00.621 --> 00:18:03.165
[YOR]
Wow. You sure know a lot, Yuri.

00:18:03.207 --> 00:18:04.542
[YOR]
Whenever I complimented him,

00:18:04.584 --> 00:18:06.460
his smile would
light up the room.

00:18:06.502 --> 00:18:10.256
[YURI] Ooh! Next, I wanna
teach you about history!

00:18:10.298 --> 00:18:11.591
[YOR]
Yeah, okay!

00:18:11.632 --> 00:18:14.552
I think he truly loved sharing
his knowledge with me,

00:18:14.594 --> 00:18:16.971
because he'd study on his
own without me pushing.

00:18:17.013 --> 00:18:20.099
[YURI] Hey, Sis, wake up!
I learned my times tables!

00:18:20.141 --> 00:18:20.891
Check it out!

00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:22.727
[YOR groans]

00:18:22.768 --> 00:18:24.103
I understand.

00:18:24.186 --> 00:18:25.896
Your approval made
a big difference.

00:18:25.938 --> 00:18:28.107
It gave him a little
extra motivation.

00:18:28.149 --> 00:18:30.151
Can't take credit for it all.

00:18:30.192 --> 00:18:32.361
But if you think
that's what helped,

00:18:32.403 --> 00:18:35.031
I don't know, maybe
you could try to play

00:18:35.072 --> 00:18:38.075
a more supportive role
like that for Anya.

00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:39.827
Praising her for little
accomplishments

00:18:39.869 --> 00:18:41.162
could make a real impact,

00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:44.665
and it's hard to see what
the downside would be.

00:18:44.707 --> 00:18:48.711
Know what I mean?
It'd make her happy.

00:18:48.753 --> 00:18:52.673
Do you think so?
Yeah, I guess you're right.

00:18:52.715 --> 00:18:55.468
[TWILIGHT] But I'm not
even her real father.

00:18:57.053 --> 00:18:59.305
[TWILIGHT]
Doesn't matter.

00:18:59.347 --> 00:19:02.725
I need to be the best
father I can for her.

00:19:02.767 --> 00:19:06.395
It's a crucial part of
the role I'm playing.

00:19:06.437 --> 00:19:09.649
It's the foundation of
the mission, after all.

00:19:09.690 --> 00:19:10.941
And I don't think
I've been taking

00:19:10.983 --> 00:19:13.402
that part of it
seriously enough.

00:19:13.444 --> 00:19:17.490
I mean, as a father,
I've been less than ideal.

00:19:17.531 --> 00:19:19.909
[YOR]
Don't worry, Loid.

00:19:19.950 --> 00:19:21.786
And have a little
faith in yourself.

00:19:21.827 --> 00:19:24.205
You remember what Anya
said about us, don't you?

00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:27.458
That we're a perfect 100 points.

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:29.377
Anya thinks you're
a wonderful father,

00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:31.712
and that's what really matters.

00:19:33.089 --> 00:19:36.050
You reminding me of that
means a great deal to me.

00:19:36.092 --> 00:19:37.009
[YOR gasps]

00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.552
I'm butting into
your family again

00:19:38.594 --> 00:19:40.680
and telling you how to
raise your daughter.

00:19:40.721 --> 00:19:43.140
Not true at all.

00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:46.185
You're not a stranger,
you're a part of this.

00:19:46.227 --> 00:19:50.523
You should know, you're the
mother of the Forger family.

00:19:50.564 --> 00:19:53.734
You provide all the things
that I never could.

00:19:53.776 --> 00:19:55.611
Yeah. Guess that's right.

00:19:55.653 --> 00:19:57.321
I forget that I'm
your wife sometimes.

00:19:57.363 --> 00:19:58.239
[TWILIGHT chuckles]

00:19:58.280 --> 00:20:01.617
Try not to say those kinds
of things outside the house.

00:20:01.659 --> 00:20:02.910
You know, it would be great

00:20:02.952 --> 00:20:04.912
if you looked over
Anya's homework, too.

00:20:04.954 --> 00:20:08.124
Oh, of course, if you think
that would be helpful.

00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:10.626
We'll work as a family,
slow and steady.

00:20:10.668 --> 00:20:14.004
[TWILIGHT] Don't panic and
take your time, Twilight.

00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:17.216
If all this could be fixed by
simply assassinating Desmond,

00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:18.884
I'd have countless options,

00:20:18.926 --> 00:20:21.929
but we're looking
for a real solution.

00:20:21.971 --> 00:20:25.349
Most things that truly
matter take time.

00:20:25.391 --> 00:20:28.185
You need to know your target's
thoughts, their desires.

00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:32.356
Use that to gain their trust so
you can observe their actions.

00:20:32.398 --> 00:20:36.318
Patience and determination
are essential to spy-craft.

00:20:36.360 --> 00:20:40.531
But first, I need
to understand Anya.

00:20:40.573 --> 00:20:41.240
[clock chimes]

00:20:41.282 --> 00:20:42.950
[TWILIGHT]
Hm?

00:20:42.992 --> 00:20:44.493
Oh my, look what time it is.

00:20:44.535 --> 00:20:47.329
I think I'll go in and have
a little chat with her.

00:20:47.371 --> 00:20:50.166
[YOR] Go ahead.
I'll take care of the dishes.

00:20:53.252 --> 00:20:55.087
Hello? Hey, Anya?

00:20:55.129 --> 00:20:57.673
Your spy cartoon's
about to start.

00:20:57.715 --> 00:20:59.341
I'm sorry about earlier.

00:20:59.383 --> 00:21:00.801
Let's watch your show first,

00:21:00.843 --> 00:21:02.219
and then we can
figure everything out

00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:03.846
with your studies.

00:21:07.391 --> 00:21:08.768
Anya?

00:21:15.274 --> 00:21:18.861
[TWILIGHT] She fell asleep.
That can't be comfortable.

00:21:20.404 --> 00:21:23.783
[TWILIGHT] She was in here
studying on her own?

00:21:23.824 --> 00:21:29.371
[ANYA] I gotta get really good
grades. Do good for Papa.

00:21:31.832 --> 00:21:35.503
[TWILIGHT] Guess I'll just
record her show for her.

00:21:35.544 --> 00:21:38.631
No, Mama. You can't kill Papa.

00:21:38.672 --> 00:21:42.551
Huh? What kind of
dream is she having?

00:21:44.428 --> 00:21:46.639
The spy man.

00:21:49.725 --> 00:21:52.978
[TWILIGHT] She thinks I'm
a wonderful father, huh?

00:21:56.148 --> 00:22:00.778
[TWILIGHT] How would it feel...
to have a real family?

00:23:37.791 --> 00:23:39.627
[DOMINIC]
Hm?

00:23:39.668 --> 00:23:42.087
Heya, Yuri! Been
working hard, huh?

00:23:42.129 --> 00:23:46.175
[YURI]
Oh, Dominic! Long time no see.

00:23:46.216 --> 00:23:47.676
They've got me so
tied up at work

00:23:47.718 --> 00:23:49.762
I haven't even been home.

00:23:49.803 --> 00:23:52.806
Sounds like the life of
a Foreign Affairs elite.

00:23:53.807 --> 00:23:54.600
Oh, yeah.

00:23:54.642 --> 00:23:57.728
I'm curious, how was the
party the other night?

00:23:57.770 --> 00:23:59.438
Was my sister's date cool?

00:23:59.480 --> 00:24:00.856
How's her date?

00:24:00.898 --> 00:24:03.734
Well, uh, guess I
should say congrats.

00:24:03.776 --> 00:24:06.737
Hold on, have you not
met her husband yet?

00:24:06.779 --> 00:24:09.281
[YURI]
Huh?

00:24:09.323 --> 00:24:13.911
What'd you say?
My sister got married?

00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:18.916
[inaudible]

